1336
01:38:17,360 --> 01:38:20,988
<i>...in the pure springs
of the southern shores...</i>

1337
01:38:21,828 --> 01:38:24,932
<i>I want to tell you that
the ocean knows this...</i>

1338
01:38:25,034 --> 01:38:30,547
<i>...that life in its jewel boxes
is endless as the sand...</i>

1339
01:38:30,622 --> 01:38:35,603
<i>...impossible to count, pure, and that
time among the blood-colored grapes...</i>

1340
01:38:37,289 --> 01:38:41,108
<i>...has made the petal hard
and shiny, filled the...</i>

1341
01:38:41,178 --> 01:38:44,614
<i>...jellyfish with light, untied its
knot letting its musical threads...</i>

1342
01:38:44,671 --> 01:38:48,959
<i>...fall from a horn of plenty
made of infinite mother-of-pearl.</i>

1343
01:38:49,701 --> 01:38:53,473
<i>I'm nothing but the empty net which
has gone on ahead of human eyes...</i>

1344
01:38:53,549 --> 01:38:56,892
<i>...dead in the darknesses, of
fingers accustomed to the triangle...</i>

1345
01:38:56,964 --> 01:39:00,044
<i>...longitudes on the
timid globe of an orange.</i>

1346
01:39:00,678 --> 01:39:04,750
<i>I walked around like you
investigating the endless star.</i>

1347
01:39:06,269 --> 01:39:10,437
<i>And in my net during the
night I woke up naked.</i>

1348
01:39:11,407 --> 01:39:20,667
<i>The only thing caught?
A fish trapped inside the wind."</i>

1349
01:39:24,008 --> 01:39:26,651
Pablo Neruda.

1350
01:39:28,854 --> 01:39:32,076
Pablo Neruda!

1351
01:39:33,033 --> 01:39:35,660
That remind you of anything?

1352
01:39:35,752 --> 01:39:39,522
"Walked around investigating the
endless star?"

1353
01:39:40,053 --> 01:39:42,573
Isn't that what you do, Sonia?

1354
01:39:42,616 --> 01:39:45,830
"And in my net during the night, I
awoke naked--" Isn't that what you do?

1355
01:39:45,893 --> 01:39:49,249
Don't you take your net and
throw it into these far-out places...

1356
01:39:49,296 --> 01:39:51,700
...of quantum physics
and systems theory?

1357
01:39:52,726 --> 01:39:55,505
And don't you find that the
only thing you ever catch...

1358
01:39:55,581 --> 01:39:57,663
...is your own self back again?

1359
01:39:59,610 --> 01:40:03,787
Like a fish trapped inside the wind?

1360
01:40:06,201 --> 01:40:12,397
Where are the other people in your
system, Sonia... the ones you love?

1361
01:40:13,793 --> 01:40:17,203
And what about these tourists
here that we feel so superior to?

1362
01:40:17,267 --> 01:40:21,213
Aren't they, too, like fish
trapped inside the wind?

1363
01:40:21,273 --> 01:40:24,236
And, I don't know, maybe even the
feeling's more terrible for them...

1364
01:40:24,293 --> 01:40:28,023
...because they don't
have words to describe it.

1365
01:40:29,492 --> 01:40:33,622
So, tell me Sonia, where
are all of us in there...

1366
01:40:34,262 --> 01:40:41,572
...the real people with their qualities,
their longings, their weaknesses?

1367
01:40:43,005 --> 01:40:47,996
Where are you inside there, Sonia?
Where's Kit?

1368
01:40:48,044 --> 01:40:51,755
You know, scientists can tell
us what life's internal...

1369
01:40:51,841 --> 01:40:55,417
...metaphors are, whether
they're computer chips or clocks.

1370
01:40:55,494 --> 01:40:59,207
Politician can tell us what
forms our lives should take...

1371
01:41:01,108 --> 01:41:03,495
But, uh...

1372
01:41:03,568 --> 01:41:09,166
I feel just as reduced being called a
system as I do being called a clock.

1373
01:41:09,226 --> 01:41:14,214
Life's just... just
not condensable.

1374
01:41:17,199 --> 01:41:20,269
One group of people uses
one set of words to change...

1375
01:41:20,344 --> 01:41:23,957
...the world, then another
set of people come along with a...

1376
01:41:24,024 --> 01:41:29,457
...different set of words to change it.
And I don't mind, you know?

1377
01:41:29,520 --> 01:41:33,425
It's all the same to me.
I don't mind a bit.

1378
01:41:33,442 --> 01:41:37,553
It's like the seasons
changing, and I like you.

1379
01:41:37,621 --> 01:41:40,394
I like your timorous courage.

1380
01:41:40,458 --> 01:41:42,968
I like the fact that you want to
make the world a better place.

1381
01:41:44,386 --> 01:41:48,267
And I like my silly friend Jack
who's crazy enough to think...

1382
01:41:48,347 --> 01:41:52,269
...that he wants to be the
president of the United States.

1383
01:41:52,357 --> 01:41:57,555
And as for me... don't mind me.
I'm a... fool.

1384
01:41:57,627 --> 01:42:02,020
But remember...

1385
01:42:02,093 --> 01:42:08,969
Life feels itself.
Life feels itself.

1386
01:42:11,195 --> 01:42:14,805
Differently, perhaps, than all your
words for how to manage it.

1387
01:42:15,483 --> 01:42:19,302
And even with the best intentions in the
world you'll go wrong if you forget...

1388
01:42:19,359 --> 01:42:22,477
...that life-- life-- life--

1389
01:42:22,557 --> 01:42:28,080
...life is infinitely more than yours
or my obtuse theories about it.

1390
01:42:28,518 --> 01:42:35,528
Healing the universe is an
inside job, and you've helped me.

1391
01:42:36,913 --> 01:42:39,385
And I love you.

1392
01:42:40,188 --> 01:42:45,086
And I love you too.
I love you both.

1393
01:42:47,390 --> 01:42:49,899
Water!

1394
01:42:50,977 --> 01:42:54,946
What a day!
What a day!

1395
01:43:52,745 --> 01:43:57,507
Well, if we're going to go,
we better leave now.

1396
01:43:57,579 --> 01:43:59,973
Why don't you just stay?

1397
01:44:00,047 --> 01:44:05,302
I don't know. Why don't you
just come? Anyway, thanks.

1398
01:44:07,814 --> 01:44:09,892
Thank you.

1399
01:44:09,949 --> 01:44:15,715
Don't thank me, I loved the day.
I hate goodbyes.

1400
01:44:15,788 --> 01:44:19,838
Maybe it's not goodbye.
Please think about what I said.

1401
01:44:21,131 --> 01:44:25,540
- Let us know how the water raises.
- Does that matter?

1402
01:44:25,601 --> 01:44:30,355
Of course it matters.
Let it get all the way back the line.

1403
01:44:30,421 --> 01:44:35,007
Let it renew itself. Right, Sonia?
Maybe come to Paris to let me know.

1404
01:44:35,109 --> 01:44:39,359
- Or Washington.
- Or New York.

1405
01:45:18,172 --> 01:45:24,556
<i>Where are the other people in your
system, Sonia... the ones you love?</i>

1406
01:45:27,377 --> 01:45:34,633
<i>The real people with their qualities...
their longings, their weaknesses.</i>

1407
01:45:34,690 --> 01:45:37,000
Mom, are you O.K.?

1408
01:45:37,076 --> 01:45:41,590
<i>Where are you inside there, Sonia?
Where's Kit?</i>

1409
01:45:50,397 --> 01:45:53,635
What are you thinking?

1410
01:46:00,167 --> 01:46:03,639
Shall we go home?

1411
01:46:23,134 --> 01:46:27,255
<i>I feel like my long weekend in France
has just come to a close.</i>

1412
01:46:27,924 --> 01:46:31,696
<i>Maybe I, too, am tired of being
a stranger, of being outside...</i>

1413
01:46:31,768 --> 01:46:37,067
<i>...a language environment which lived,
which resonated inside me...</i>

1414
01:46:37,551 --> 01:46:42,722
<i>...our emotional system, as she might
say, needs a larger system to nurture it.</i>

1415
01:46:48,346 --> 01:46:49,880
<i>Doesn't make any difference.</i>

1416
01:46:49,939 --> 01:46:53,008
<i>You're locked in with the people you know,
you need to belong somewhere.</i>

1417
01:46:53,074 --> 01:46:56,321
<i>- He's right, of course,
about damn near everything.</i>

1418
01:46:56,881 --> 01:47:00,579
<i>Even the parts I didn't
understand felt right.</i>

1419
01:47:01,652 --> 01:47:07,327
<i>So... should
I just go with it?</i>

1420
01:47:08,978 --> 01:47:11,588
<i>Is this one of those turning points?</i>

1421
01:47:17,972 --> 01:47:24,700
<i>"You the woman, I the man, this the
world, and each is the work of all.</i>

1422
01:47:25,268 --> 01:47:28,535
<i>It is the muffled step in the sand,
the stranger, the crippled wren...</i>

1423
01:47:28,614 --> 01:47:31,655
<i>...the nun, the dance of the angels,
winging over the walkers in the village.</i>

1424
01:47:31,727 --> 01:47:35,483
<i>And there are many beautiful arms
around us and the things we know..."</i>

1425
01:47:36,883 --> 01:47:41,262
<i>I don't know how the
rest of that damn poem goes.</i>

